What is express?
- Expresss is a minimal node.js framework, a higher level of abstraction
- Express contains a very  robust set of features: complex routing, easier handling of requests and responses, middleware, server-side rendering, etc;
- Express allows for rapid development of node,js applications: we dont hanve to reinvent the wheel;
- Express makes it easiwe to organize out application into the MVC architecture.'

THE REST ARCHITECTURE
----
- Try to keep the endpoints as the resource names. We dont need to make endpoint names assosiated with the correctsponding method. 
- Separate API into logical resources.
- Expose structured, resource-based URLs
- Use HTTP methods (verbs)
- Send data s JSON
- Be stateless
